Police in Westenburg outside Polokwane have arrested an off-duty Traffic officer aged 42-year-old after he shot a 17-year-old girl. It is alleged that three minor girls aged 13, 15 and 17 were walking along the street when the suspect insulted them. An exchange of words ensued between the man and the youngsters until he chased them with his motor vehicle. The suspect apparently fired several shots in the direction of the children injuring a 17-year-old girl in the process. Police and Medical Emergency Services were summoned and immediately responded leading to the apprehension of the suspect and the confiscation of his private firearm. The victim was rushed to the local hospital where she was treated and is recuperating at home. The police are still investigating the matter to establish the circumstances of the shooting. -Afro Voice Reporter 